values:
Ganito naman talaga ang pag-ibig db? Minsan may naffriendzone ka na gusto ka pala at gusto mo pala talaga. Minsan ayaw ka ng gusto mo. Minsan ayaw mo ng gusto ka. Minsan di lang talaga kayo sabay na pwede.
Pero ganun talaga ang buhay db? I can't have everything. My life isn't like a movie. It's not like the books I read. I can't watch life happen by the sidelines, thinking I won't get hurt or I'll be wiser by living vicariously. Because I have to live my own life.

Yeah, I think this is what I'm supposed to learn from all of this heartache. I must not live vicariously. I must learn how to love, not to be in love vicariously.
Babe, it's a second night. It's too much already. It's distracting me already

And true love waits.

Too bad I already found the love of my life.
He's my greatest love too.
I hope he's my true love too.

I miss you. I'm still trying to forgive myself. But at the end of the road, I still hope it's you.

I'm doing better, I think. I even fancy myself over you.

I hope
I wish
My love

I lost you again.

and this time, it <strike>might</strike> be permanent.

I always pray that the Lord will guide you and send you His angels to take care of you, make sure you're alright and safe. I think I know why these happened to me, to us, and I'm slowly learning all of it. and with that...

It was only just a dream.

This is my reality. 24/7 on call to the hospital. A social/extra-hospital life, as I coin it today, that is semi-nonexistent. Based in the city. Coming home soon to the province, I hope. Friends who I know I can trust and yet I can't tell them much about this insecurity/sadness/loneliness. Family waiting for me to pass the boards. Board exam this August. Patients hoping I'll be able to help them ease their burden.

It was only just a dream

Hotel room nights. Laughter and silly things. Tango calls. Skype calls. Emails and FB messages. Tango messages. Dog tags and stickers. Trip around ships with planes. Holding hands.

It was only just a dream

Posted via LiveJournal app for iPhone.

Too lazy to do anything. Too alone to be anywhere. So here I am stuck at home, having the "me" time people have been telling me to get. But it sucks big time, because I don't get anything done. I watch TV all day, think about ... yes, him. And wonder if the other guy will really look my way. The truth is I still love him. The sad part is I'm hoping that the other guy will wait for me. Him. Navyguy. Other guy. ArtistaLookalike. As much as I want to move on, I can't just forget that I love him. And I can't redirect this love to the other guy because he deserves something more than this. If we are to be together, we deserve something more. Gusto kong sabihin sa'yo na walang magagalit na tayo ang magka-date, wala nang magagalit. Ang tanong e sa'yo ba ay magagalit pa?

I used to make lists of what I want in a guy but I end up breaking them. I know I'll break them anyway but it is fun making them.

So when a guy who got all the check on my list came along, any girl would grab that opportunity. But I was dead wrong.

Lists were wishes. Fairytales say wishes do come true. But the Lord always has something better.

I'm not sure if this is what I should be learning from all of this chaos but that's what I am getting from all of it. No matter how long my list can be, no matter how many checks the guy can have on that it list, it doesn't mean that he is the one. He is the one I want. But like everything I have right now, it may be not the ones I want but they definitely are the ones I need.

Posted via LiveJournal app for iPhone.

How to move on from this (i.e. how to get over the greatest love I had) 1. Listen to Maroon 5       And when the daylight comes I have to go, but tonight I'm gonna hold you so close       I never knew perfection until I heard you speak       Better that we break? :( 2. Watch Pitch Perfect... over and over and over and over    Since you've been gone I can breath for the first time 3. Listen to some Lenka too     Don't let me fall 4. Keep busy     Ward na lang ako forever please? Ward-SICU lang ako. Kahit sliding. 5. Prettify yourself Buy face powder. Check. Wear BB cream as regular as I can. Check. Need to buy new BB cream. Suggestions? How not to get over? Get a new love life. Meet someone new. Bad ideas! I had my first love. I now I have my greatest love. I hope the next one's my true love. I'm always hopeful like that. But this is too great to let go just like that. Someday, I'll get over and move on. Someday, I'll be fine. Someday, I'll be better. When that time comes, I hope my true love is ready too.

If You Forget Me (Pablo Neruda)

I want you to know
one thing.

You know how this is:
if I look
at the crystal moon, at the red branch
of the slow autumn at my window,
if I touch
near the fire the impalpable ash or the wrinkled body of the log, everything carries me to you, as if everything that exists, aromas, light, metals, were little boats that sail toward those isles of yours that wait for me. Well, now, if little by little you stop loving me I shall stop loving you little by little. If suddenly you forget me do not look for me, for I shall already have forgotten you. If you think it long and mad, the wind of banners that passes through my life, and you decide to leave me at the shore of the heart where I have roots, remember that on that day, at that hour, I shall lift my arms and my roots will set off to seek another land. But if each day, each hour, you feel that you are destined for me with implacable sweetness, if each day a flower climbs up to your lips to seek me, ah my love, ah my own, in me all that fire is repeated, in me nothing is extinguished or forgotten, my love feeds on your love, beloved, and as long as you live it will be in your arms without leaving mine. You just die everyday. You live by the moment. Every moment, it takes your breathe away literally.

Ang hirap sabihin na mahal kita. Mahal kita. Mahal kita? Mahal kita! Parang kapag pinapa-ulit-ulit ko siyang isipin nagiging walang kabuluhan, walang kwenta, walang saysay ang mga salita. Ibig sabihin ba nun totoo ung nararamdaman ko? Na... Mahal nga kita?

Hindi kita mahal. Ayan. May katuturan na. Nakikita ko ung kahulugan nya. Hindi kita mahal. Parang kapag pinapa-ulit-ulit ko siyang isipin, alam kong sa puso ko un ung totoo. 'Yun ang nararamdaman ko.

Subalit nasasaktan ako. Kapag naiisip kita, gusto kitang makasama. Gusto ko nandiyan ka. Gusto ko nandiyan ako sa tabi mo. Sana nasa tabi kita. 'Yung ikaw ung una kong sasabihan ng mga bagay na naiiisip ko kahit na ano pang mangyari. 'Yung tipong shet di ko mabitawan ang kapit ko. 'Yung tipong....sasabihan ko ng.... sana ako na lang. Sana ako.

Masama mang tignan dahil mukhang pinagsisiksikan ko ang sarili ko sa isang masikip na lugar. Parang kapag sasakay ng jeep at ako ung huling pasahero. Ung tipong 1/4 na lang pwet ung nakaupo. Mahirap pero pinipilit. Pero mas ok pa ata ung sa jeep kasi alam ko may baba o alam kong baba din naman ako mamaya. Sa'yo? Di ko alam kung may aalis. At di ko din alam kung kaya kong umalis.

Paano ako aalis? Paano ako bibitaw? Iniisip ko pa lang na kailangan kong bumitaw, lalong humihigpit ang kapit ko. Lalong hindi ako makabitaw. Mahal nga ba kita?

Mababaw lamang ang mga luha sa aking mata. Mababaw lang ang hapdi sa aking puso. Sumasakit lang ang ulo ko kapag iniisip kita. At nanghihina ang mga tuhod ko sa posibilidad pa lang na makita kita. Iniisip ko pa lang na hindi na kita makikita kahit kailan, gusto ko nang matulog habang buhay at hindi na lang gumising. Gusto ko na lang humilata sa kama at matulog...at managinip...baka sakali nandun ka. Alam kong nandun ka. Nandun ung halakhak mo. Nandun ung ngiti mo. Nandun ung HHWW. Nandun ung halik mo. Nandun ung yakap mo. At higit sa lahat....nandun (sana) ang pag-ibig mo. 
Pero alam kong hindi kita mahal.

Iniibig kita.

Alam ko na!
Iniibig kita.

Nandyan na ang pag-agos ng luha. Nandyan na ang malalim na sugat ng puso. Nandiyan na ang hindi mawari ng ulirat. Nandyan na ang panghihina ng buong katawan.

Ngunit hanggang dyan lang. Hanggang dyan na lamang.

Sabi ng isang picture sa Facebook, uso na ngayon ang moving on kahit hindi naging kayo.

This is one of those good days even though I remember things about him...It's one of those days that memories of him are not painful. On our last night together, I said that he's lucky because he's got so many girls...and one of them is a doctor. He laughed. It's kind of a nervous laugh. But he knows what I mean... I think.

"Love is a battlefield", anyways.

The proverb does not only apply to father but also to a certain co-intern and to a certain military guy. And maybe up to a certain point, for a certain seafarer. But alas (whoa!), good things come to an end. And it ends up with me disappointing myself. Always coming short of that one thing I dreamed of, wanted, sometimes need.

Lesson #4:Never assume. Yes, even though he teases you all the time, he takes special time with you, calms you down when you're stressed, replies to your messages, hears your every whine, even complies to your every whim, maybe even adores you and thinks your cute, until he says that he like likes you, he DOES NOT LIKE you. Even if your friends tell you he might and looks like he likes you. Well, maybe unless your pretty or beautiful then you are sure he would say he likes you too. But yes, I am not even close to being cute, let alone pretty and even beautiful, so us mere mortals have to wait for our knight in shining armor or prince charming to rescue us and profess their undying love and even slay the dragon until we'll have our happily ever after... unless the witch or evil stepmother or stepsisters got to him first. Too bad for us because we might be ending up with ogres who don't deserve us or not even close to a gentlemen as Shrek is.

Lesson #2: But if you just keep moving, you will come to a better place. - Iroh, Avatar S02E19

It will be a hard battle. It won't be easy. There will be times when you want to stop and go back to where you started. Times when relapse is the only choice. Times when you want to cry and you know he is the only one who can comfort you. Really. But be strong like a rock. You will come to a better place. Better than you expected it to be. Especially if thru this road, you'll learn more about yourself. And how strong you really are.

And yes, it may seem that your heart has hardened. That you feel you won't love anymore. That you don't know how to love anymore.

It isn't. You aren't. You are strong. You are a rock that you can depend on. You can depend on yourself.

Lesson #3:There will be good days and bad days. And it's up to you to choose them. Bad days may come but it's up to you to change it into a good one. No one, nobody, is trying to make the day bad for you, reminding you of the sad stuff. It's just coincidence. Sometimes, it's the Lord's way of saying this is how far you've come, or testing you to let you know how much you've gone ahead in this moving on/letting go. There's a rainbow after the rain. And there's a pot of gold at the end of the rainbow. Bad days may come. Rainy days are inevitable. But there are also good days to help you get through. Your life isn't that-place-where-Bella-Swan-and-Edward-Cullen-lives-where-it's-dark-more-than-half-of-the-year. It is your life. Yours given by the Lord.

Fighting with a close friend is something that drains you, and demands of both of you to rise to the occasion and swallow your pride, even if you believe you were 100 percent right. Whether it’s over a broken promise, a told secret, a love interest, or anything in between, few things are harder because you know that, under any other circumstances, they would be the person you called to get advice from/vent to.

I hate it when I'm guarded... and you give me all the space I want. No, don't give me all the space I want.

Love comes in unexpected places, in unexpected ways.
I wish. I hope.
Come back and stay.
